<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,522,1820]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,477,597,623]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The male imago can be separated from other Neotropical species of the genus by the combination of gonostylus furcate with secondary lobe shorter than main lobe, anal point present and median volsella composed of a single branch.
</paragraph>
